Package controlPanel

Class ScheduleControl

java.lang.Object
controlPanel.ScheduleControl
public class ScheduleControl
extends java.lang.Object
The ScheduleControl contains on the communication methods between the Control Panel to the server for Schedule Methods. It includes methods which will use functions from helpers that initialises communication and returns relevant object from server or server acknowledgements, such as creating, editing, removing Schedules.

    • scheduleBillboardRequest

      public static java.lang.String scheduleBillboardRequest​(java.lang.String sessionToken, java.lang.String billboardName, java.lang.String startTime, java.lang.Integer Duration, java.lang.String CreationDateTime, java.lang.Integer Repeat, java.lang.Integer Sunday, java.lang.Integer Monday, java.lang.Integer Tuesday, java.lang.Integer Wednesday, java.lang.Integer Thursday, java.lang.Integer Friday, java.lang.Integer Saturday) throws java.io.IOException, java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
      Send Queries: Schedule Creation. This is a generic method which sends a create billboard Schedule request from control panel to server.

      This method always returns immediately.

      Parameters:
      sessionToken - A String which represents the sessionToken generated when logged in.
      billboardName - A String which represents the billboard name to schedule.
      startTime - A String in format of Java Time to store into database.
      Duration - An Integer representing an integer which provides Duration which to store into database.
      CreationDateTime - A String in format of DateTime which provides CreationDateTime to store into database.
      Repeat - An Integer representing an integer how often the schedule is repeated (in minutes).
      Sunday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Sunday.
      Monday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Monday.
      Tuesday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Tuesday.
      Wednesday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Wednesday.
      Thursday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Thursday.
      Friday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Friday.
      Saturday - An Integer that's either 1 or 0 to see if the schedule is to be run during Saturday.
      Returns:
      A String which is an acknowledgement message from the server.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - Throws an exception if an I/O exception of some sort has occurred.
      java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - Throws an exception when a specified class cannot be found in the classpath.
